text: Eudonia tibetalis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Aristide Caradja in 1937. It is found in the Chinese provinces of Qinghai, Sichuan and Yunnan., 2012: One new species of the genus Eudonia Billberg (Lepidoptera: Crambidae: Scopariinae) from China. Entomotaxonomia 34 (2): 267-269. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1937 Category:Scopariinae
title: Eudonia tibetalis
